[Given the WHO decision to refer to this outbreak by the identified novel coronavirus, we will be changing the thread name of the reports to reflect this: "Novel coronavirus - China: (Hubei).

In summary, there are currently 41 individuals confirmed as part of the Wuhan CoV outbreak including one fatality with an individual with serious pre-existing co-morbidities. There are 7 individuals in serious condition. Six individuals have been discharged from the hospital. Dates of onset of the cases ranged from [8 Dec 2019] to [2 Jan 2020], with no additional cases detected since [3 Jan 2020]. 763 individuals with identified close contact with the cases are under observation (including medical staff); no secondary cases have been identified.

It is too early to breathe a collective sigh of relief, as tempting as it may be. There are other wet markets in China that may have animals from the same area. We still do not know the host or possible intermediary host of this virus. And with the coming Chinese New Year (25 Jan 2020), there will be massive population movement in the country and the region, and wildlife meals are delicacies...

A map showing locations of major cities in China can be found at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/city-maps.html.
HealthMap/ProMED-mail map: Hubei, China: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6885385,5294. - Mod.MPP]

