Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It is not surprising that the suspected cases of pneumonia identified in Singapore, Hong Kong and Bangkok have tested negative for the coronavirus as none of the patients gave a history of contact with the implicated Seafood Market, and the outbreak at present seems to have been contained to individuals with contact in the Seafood Market.

With respect to the phylogenetic anlayses, EcoHealth Alliance posted findings of preliminary phylogenetic analysis of the genome of the Wuhan CoV (the phylogenetic tree is available at https://www.ecohealthalliance.org/2020/01/phylogenetic-analysis-shows-novel-wuhan-coronavirus-clusters-with-sars). According to EcoHealth Alliance: "The coronavirus genome was released by the Shanghai Public Health Clinical Center & School of Public Health, in collaboration with the Central Hospital of Wuhan, Huazhong University of Science and Technology, the Wuhan Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the National Institute for Communicable Disease Control and Prevention, Chinese Center for Disease Control, and the University of Sydney, Sydney, Australia. It can be accessed and downloaded at http://virological.org/t/initial-genome-release-of-novel-coronavirus/319.

Twitter discussions have raised the observation that it appears as though this outbreak was associated with a single spillover from the animal hosts due to non-divergence of the genomes (https://twitter.com/arambaut/status/1216026183118344196). - Mod.MPP]
